<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{2}{y}=-{42}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}-{6}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({6},-{6}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{2}{y}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{42}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{42}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{\left(\frac{{-{42}-{\left({2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}\right)}+-{6}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{9}}{{-{{5}}}}\cdot{\left(-{42}\right)}--\frac{{9}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left({2}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{75.6}-{\left(-{3.6}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3.6}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}=-{18}--{75.6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{3.6}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}={57.6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3.6}+{\left(-{6}\right)}\right)}{y}={57.6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9.6}{y}={57.6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{57.6}}{{-{{9.6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{2}{\left(-{6}\right)}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left(-{12}\right)}=-{42}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{42}-{\left(-{12}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{30}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={6}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({6},-{6}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

